  "title": "Repair & Development Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>In charge of conducting and certify scheduled and unscheduled maintenance, repair, and testing of aircraft systems and components.</li>\n  <li>Responsible for carrying out complex tasks such as engine servicing and component replacement, troubleshooting defects, and maintaining production equipment.</li>\n  <li>In charge of performing detailed inspections of aircraft structures, landing gear, engines, and other critical systems.</li>\n  <li>In charge of leading and supervising teams of technicians to complete maintenance tasks efficiently.</li>\n  <li>Responsible in promoting and upholding a culture of safety among maintenance teams and ensure all activities comply with quality standards.</li>\n  <li>Maintain detailed and accurate records of all maintenance activities and certifications.</li>\n  <li>Ensure all work is performed in accordance with regulations from the Civil Aviation Authority (CAA) and the Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirement:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum Degree in Mechanical/Manufacturing/Aeronautical Engineering or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 3 years of working experience in MRO industry</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of special processes such as Weldng (TIG/EBW), Thermal Spray, Heat Treatment,  Machining will be advantage</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>To submit your application, please apply online to <a href=\"mailto:apply@rn-care.com\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>apply@rn-care.com </strong></a>or call +(65) <a href=\"tel:6513 5697\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>6513 5697</strong></a> for private and confidential discussion.</p>\n<p>Your interest will be treated with the strictest of confidence. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified or contacted.</p>\n<p><strong>RN Care Pte. Ltd</strong><br>\n<strong>EA License No: 17C8900</strong></p>",
